==English==

===Etymology===
In reference to a punishment once meted out to heretics. <!--Chambers 1908-->

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|en-au-haul someone over the coals.ogg|Audio (AU)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|*|head=[[haul]] [[someone]] [[over]] the [[coal]]s}}

# {{lb|en|chiefly|UK|idiomatic}} To express [[anger]] with someone [[in no uncertain terms]] when they do something wrong.
#: ''The teacher '''hauled him over the coals''' for not doing his homework.''

